# Repos this hub coordinates. One per line; `make repos` reads this file.
#
# Format:  canonical:clone_dir:github_repo:kind
#   canonical    — name under ./repos (what you cd into from the hub)
#   clone_dir    — directory name inside the clone workspace (may differ from canonical)
#   github_repo  — repo name to clone if clone_dir is missing (under $HUB_ORG)
#   kind         — informational tag (service|infra|web|lib|gitops|…)
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
#
# TEMPLATE: replace the examples below with the project's real repos. For a single-repo
# project, delete this file (and scripts/repos.sh + the Makefile repo targets).

{{repo-a}}:{{repo-a}}:{{repo-a}}:service
{{repo-b}}:{{clone-dir-b}}:{{repo-b}}:web
